                <head>273. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 13 <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Herman Phleger</persName> delivered an
                    address before the American Branch of the International Law Association in New
                    York City entitled “Recent Developments Affecting the Regime of the High Seas.”
                    Among the matters discussed by <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName>
                    were freedom of the seas, conservation of fishery resources, and the Continental
                    Shelf. The text of the address is printed in Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 6, 1955, pages 934-940.</p>
            </div>
